<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0"><channel><item><title>A New Build System For This Website</title><link>https://vibe-876.github.io/posts/building-the-website.html</link><description>>:3</description><content type="html"><p>My website started with just HTML I wrote, with a bit of CSS. But I
don't really like HTML, and I do like really GNU Emacs, so I started
using Org Mode, exporting each bit manually. But I don't really like
doing the same thing over and over and over again, so I wrote a bash
script to handle it for me.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre
class="sourceCode bash"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#!/bin/bash</span></span>
<span id="cb1-2"><a href="#cb1-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-3"><a href="#cb1-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-4"><a href="#cb1-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="bu">echo</span> <span class="st">&quot;&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;title&gt;Blog&lt;/title&gt;&lt;link rel=</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st">stylesheet</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st"> href=</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st">styles.css</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st">&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Blog Entries&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;a href=</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st">index.html</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st">&gt;Back Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&quot;</span> <span class="op">&gt;</span> blog.html</span>
<span id="cb1-5"><a href="#cb1-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-6"><a href="#cb1-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="va">pages</span><span class="op">=</span><span class="va">$(</span><span class="fu">find</span> ./posts <span class="at">-type</span> f <span class="at">-iname</span> <span class="dt">\*</span>.org <span class="kw">|</span> <span class="fu">sort</span><span class="va">)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-7"><a href="#cb1-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="cf">for</span> page <span class="kw">in</span> <span class="va">$pages</span></span>
<span id="cb1-8"><a href="#cb1-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="cf">do</span></span>
<span id="cb1-9"><a href="#cb1-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="bu">echo</span> <span class="st">&quot;Building </span><span class="va">$page</span><span class="st">...&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb1-10"><a href="#cb1-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="ex">pandoc</span> <span class="va">$page</span> <span class="at">-o</span> .<span class="va">$(</span><span class="bu">echo</span> <span class="va">$page</span> <span class="kw">|</span> <span class="fu">cut</span> <span class="at">-f2</span> <span class="at">-d</span><span class="st">&#39;.&#39;</span><span class="va">)</span>.html <span class="at">--css</span><span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&quot;../styles.css&quot;</span> <span class="at">-s</span></span>
<span id="cb1-11"><a href="#cb1-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-12"><a href="#cb1-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="va">pagename</span><span class="op">=</span>.<span class="va">$(</span><span class="bu">echo</span> <span class="va">$page</span> <span class="kw">|</span> <span class="fu">cut</span> <span class="at">-f2</span> <span class="at">-d</span><span class="st">&#39;.&#39;</span><span class="va">)</span>.html</span>
<span id="cb1-13"><a href="#cb1-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="va">pagetitle</span><span class="op">=</span><span class="va">$(</span><span class="fu">grep</span> <span class="st">&quot;#+title&quot;</span> <span class="va">$page</span> <span class="kw">|</span> <span class="fu">cut</span> <span class="at">-f2-</span> <span class="at">-d</span><span class="st">&#39; &#39;</span> <span class="kw">|</span> <span class="fu">head</span> <span class="at">-n1</span><span class="va">)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-14"><a href="#cb1-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="va">pagedate</span><span class="op">=</span><span class="va">$(</span><span class="fu">grep</span> <span class="st">&quot;#+date&quot;</span> <span class="va">$page</span> <span class="kw">|</span> <span class="fu">cut</span> <span class="at">-f2</span> <span class="at">-d</span><span class="st">&#39; &#39;</span><span class="va">)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-15"><a href="#cb1-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="bu">echo</span> <span class="st">&quot;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="va">$pagename</span><span class="dt">\&quot;</span><span class="st">&gt;</span><span class="va">$pagetitle</span><span class="st">, </span><span class="va">$pagedate</span><span class="st">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&quot;</span> <span class="op">&gt;&gt;</span> blog.html</span>
<span id="cb1-16"><a href="#cb1-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="cf">done</span></span>
<span id="cb1-17"><a href="#cb1-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-18"><a href="#cb1-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="bu">echo</span> <span class="st">&quot;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&quot;</span> <span class="op">&gt;&gt;</span> blog.html</span>
<span id="cb1-19"><a href="#cb1-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-20"><a href="#cb1-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-21"><a href="#cb1-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="ex">pandoc</span> index.org <span class="at">-o</span> index.html <span class="at">--css</span><span class="op">=</span><span class="st">&quot;styles.css&quot;</span> <span class="at">-s</span></span></code></pre></div>
<p>It's not the most elegant thing in the word, but it does the trick.
Besides, bash is just about never elegant anyway, that's what I like
about it – like a more cursed perl.</p>
<p>Maybe now that I just run a script to setup my website, I might even
start actually putting something on this blog! Might even make an RSS
feed too, but not yet…</p>
<p>I also might end up automating the part where I push to Github, but
not yet.</p>
</content></item><item><title>Using Maven</title><link>https://vibe-876.github.io/posts/maven-guide.html</link><description>>:3</description><content type="html"><h1 id="what-is-this">What is This</h1>
<p>I need to do a group project in Javafor uni, and as a team, we
decided on using Maven. However, not everyone on the team knows how to
use Maven, so I've written this up – I hope that it can be useful for
you.</p>
<h1 id="what-is-maven">What is Maven</h1>
<p>Apache Maven is a build system for (among other languages) Java. It
describes how the system should be built using <a
href="https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/">XML</a> (eXtensible Markup
Language), as well as any dependencies the project needs, and any
plugins Maven should be using. This all goes into a file called
<code>pom.xml</code>, in the root of your project's directory.</p>
<h1 id="a-basic-example">A Basic Example</h1>
<p>Suppose we have some project – we may lay out the build file like
this.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre
class="sourceCode xml"><code class="sourceCode xml"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;<span class="kw">project</span> <span class="ot">xmlns=</span><span class="st">&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb1-2"><a href="#cb1-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>         <span class="ot">xmlns:xsi=</span><span class="st">&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb1-3"><a href="#cb1-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>         <span class="ot">xsi:schemaLocation=</span><span class="st">&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0</span></span>
<span id="cb1-4"><a href="#cb1-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">               http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd&quot;</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-5"><a href="#cb1-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">modelVersion</span>&gt;4.0.0&lt;/<span class="kw">modelVersion</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-6"><a href="#cb1-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;com.gpseven&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-7"><a href="#cb1-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;GPSeven&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-8"><a href="#cb1-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;0.0.1&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-9"><a href="#cb1-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">build</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-10"><a href="#cb1-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">plugins</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-11"><a href="#cb1-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">plugin</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-12"><a href="#cb1-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-13"><a href="#cb1-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-14"><a href="#cb1-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;3.1.0&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-15"><a href="#cb1-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">configuration</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-16"><a href="#cb1-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">archive</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-17"><a href="#cb1-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">manifest</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-18"><a href="#cb1-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        &lt;<span class="kw">addClasspath</span>&gt;true&lt;/<span class="kw">addClasspath</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-19"><a href="#cb1-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        &lt;<span class="kw">mainClass</span>&gt;uk.ac.aber.cs221.group07.Graphics.Main&lt;/<span class="kw">mainClass</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-20"><a href="#cb1-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;/<span class="kw">manifest</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-21"><a href="#cb1-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;/<span class="kw">archive</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-22"><a href="#cb1-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;/<span class="kw">configuration</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-23"><a href="#cb1-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;/<span class="kw">plugin</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-24"><a href="#cb1-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-25"><a href="#cb1-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">plugin</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-26"><a href="#cb1-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.openjfx&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-27"><a href="#cb1-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;javafx-maven-plugin&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-28"><a href="#cb1-28" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;0.0.8&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-29"><a href="#cb1-29" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">configuration</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-30"><a href="#cb1-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">mainClass</span>&gt;uk.ac.aber.cs221.group07.Graphics.Main&lt;/<span class="kw">mainClass</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-31"><a href="#cb1-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;/<span class="kw">configuration</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-32"><a href="#cb1-32" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;/<span class="kw">plugin</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-33"><a href="#cb1-33" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;/<span class="kw">plugins</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-34"><a href="#cb1-34" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;/<span class="kw">build</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-35"><a href="#cb1-35" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-36"><a href="#cb1-36" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">dependencies</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-37"><a href="#cb1-37" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-38"><a href="#cb1-38" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-39"><a href="#cb1-39" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;junit-jupiter-api&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-40"><a href="#cb1-40" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;5.2.0&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-41"><a href="#cb1-41" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">scope</span>&gt;test&lt;/<span class="kw">scope</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-42"><a href="#cb1-42" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;/<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-43"><a href="#cb1-43" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-44"><a href="#cb1-44" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-45"><a href="#cb1-45" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.openjfx&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-46"><a href="#cb1-46" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;javafx-controls&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-47"><a href="#cb1-47" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;25.0.2&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-48"><a href="#cb1-48" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;/<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-49"><a href="#cb1-49" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;/<span class="kw">dependencies</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb1-50"><a href="#cb1-50" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;/<span class="kw">project</span>&gt;</span></code></pre></div>
<p>Pretty scary right. This is the <code>pom.xml</code> file for a
project I'm doing at university for a <a
href="https://www.aber.ac.uk/en/modules/deptcurrent/CS22120/AB2/">module</a>.</p>
<p>Notice how we're <em>not</em> specifying where to find the source
code, like we would in say, Apache Ant, GNU Makefiles, or a <a
href="http://www.catb.org/~esr/jargon/html/P/Perl.html">hacked-together
perl scsript</a>. Maven goes for <u>convention over configuration</u>,
and defaults to the following structures:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Directory Name</th>
<th>Purpose</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>./</code></td>
<td>The root of the project, and where <code>pom.xml</code> lives</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>src/main/java/</code></td>
<td>Contains the deliverable Java code</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>src/main/resources/</code></td>
<td>Contains the deliverable resources</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>src/test/java/</code></td>
<td>Contains the tests (Junit tests, in our case)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>src/test/resources/</code></td>
<td>Contains resources for the tests</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>We can then compile our program using the <code>mvn compile</code>
command. This will – if it doesn't already exist – create
<code>target/</code>, a directory in which all class files go, as well
as any jars that may be generated.</p>
<h1 id="maven-commands">Maven Commands</h1>
<p>Maven has many built in commands, and we can add more by using
plugins. Some of the basic and most useful commands are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>mvn compile</code> Compiles the source into class files</li>
<li><code>mvn package</code> Compiles the source into a jar file</li>
<li><code>mvn install</code> Install the package in the local Maven
repository</li>
<li><code>mvn clean</code> Remove build files from
<code>target/</code></li>
</ul>
<p>If you're using IntelliJ, congratulations, you don't really need to
use these commands, as it'll be handled by IntelliJ. However, if you're
using another editor (say, GNU Emacs), then you may need to do this
yourself (if you're a fellow Emacs lover, then I'd recommend just using
<code>M-x compile</code>, and running Maven commands through that – I
might write a <a href="https://github.com/magit/transient">transient</a>
menu for it at some point). We can also add some more commands, using
the amazing magic of ✨ <em>plugins</em> ✨.</p>
<h2 id="plugins">Plugins</h2>
<p>I have some projects I have to do for uni, some of which require <a
href="https://openjfx.io/">JavaFX</a> (ew). To do this, we use a
plugin.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2"><pre
class="sourceCode xml"><code class="sourceCode xml"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;<span class="kw">plugins</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">plugin</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-3"><a href="#cb2-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.openjfx&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-4"><a href="#cb2-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;javafx-maven-plugin&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-5"><a href="#cb2-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;0.0.8&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-6"><a href="#cb2-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">configuration</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-7"><a href="#cb2-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>      &lt;<span class="kw">mainClass</span>&gt;io.github.vibe-876.Graphics.Main&lt;/<span class="kw">mainClass</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-8"><a href="#cb2-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;/<span class="kw">configuration</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-9"><a href="#cb2-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;/<span class="kw">plugin</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb2-10"><a href="#cb2-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;/<span class="kw">plugins</span>&gt;</span></code></pre></div>
<p>We can now run <code>mvn javafx:run</code>, and our JavaFX plugin
will be started! (Okay, technically we also need to include JavaFX as a
dependency, but I'm covering that in the next section, not here).</p>
<h2 id="dependencies">Dependencies</h2>
<p>Suppose I have some project, for which I want to use Junit 5, and
Maven. But oh no! I can't run that directly through Maven, whatever
shall I do :'( ! Thankfully, dependencies come to the rescue; for our
Junit example, we could include something like this</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb3"><pre
class="sourceCode xml"><code class="sourceCode xml"><span id="cb3-1"><a href="#cb3-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;<span class="kw">dependencies</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-2"><a href="#cb3-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-3"><a href="#cb3-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-4"><a href="#cb3-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;junit-jupiter-api&lt;/<span class="kw">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-5"><a href="#cb3-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;5.2.0&lt;/<span class="kw">version</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-6"><a href="#cb3-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">scope</span>&gt;test&lt;/<span class="kw">scope</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-7"><a href="#cb3-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;/<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb3-8"><a href="#cb3-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;/<span class="kw">dependencies</span>&gt;</span></code></pre></div>
<p>We can now run <code>mvn test</code>, and all tests within
<code>src/test/java/</code> will be ran.</p>
<p>If we also want to include, say, JavaFX, we can add that as a
dependency too!</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb4"><pre
class="sourceCode xml"><code class="sourceCode xml"><span id="cb4-1"><a href="#cb4-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>&lt;<span class="kw">dependencies</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb4-2"><a href="#cb4-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  &lt;<span class="kw">dependency</span>&gt;</span>
<span id="cb4-3"><a href="#cb4-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    &lt;<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/<span class="kw">groupId</span>&gt;</span>
